WEBVTT

00:00.000 --> 00:04.920
CHAPTERS 1 AND 2 OF THE GOSPEL OF MARK.

00:22.780 --> 00:25.980
THE GOSPEL OF MARK.

00:25.980 --> 00:29.800
King James Version, Chapter 1.

00:30.360 --> 00:35.500
The beginning of the Gospel of Jesus Christ, the Son of God.

00:36.040 --> 00:38.220
As it is written in the prophets,

00:38.540 --> 00:42.240
Behold, I send my messenger before thy face,

00:42.780 --> 00:45.600
Which shall prepare thy way before thee,

00:46.120 --> 00:49.620
The voice of one crying in the wilderness,

00:50.140 --> 00:53.460
Prepare ye the way of the Lord,

00:53.460 --> 00:56.260
Make his path straight.

00:57.140 --> 00:59.440
John did baptize in the wilderness,

00:59.960 --> 01:03.300
And preach the baptism of repentance

01:03.300 --> 01:05.600
For the remission of sins.

01:06.040 --> 01:11.140
And there went out unto him all the land of Judea,

01:11.300 --> 01:13.080
And they of Jerusalem,

01:13.480 --> 01:18.140
And were all baptized of him in the river of Jordan,

01:18.400 --> 01:20.220
Confessing their sins.

01:20.620 --> 01:24.300
And John was clothed with camel's hair,

01:24.640 --> 01:28.840
And with a girdle of a skin about his loins,

01:29.300 --> 01:32.900
And he did eat locusts and wild honey,

01:33.540 --> 01:35.020
And preached, saying,

01:35.500 --> 01:37.500
There cometh one mightier than I,

01:37.700 --> 01:40.740
After me, the latchet of whose shoes,

01:41.040 --> 01:46.180
I am not worthy to stoop down and unloose.

01:46.720 --> 01:50.060
I indeed have baptized you with water,

01:50.380 --> 01:55.060
But he shall baptize you with the Holy Ghost.

01:55.760 --> 01:57.860
And it came to pass in those days

01:57.860 --> 02:02.420
That Jesus came from Nazareth of Galilee,

02:02.740 --> 02:05.640
And was baptized of John in Jordan,

02:06.040 --> 02:09.020
And straightway coming up out of the water,

02:09.440 --> 02:11.540
He saw the heavens opened,

02:11.540 --> 02:16.040
And the Spirit, like a dove, descending upon him.

02:16.300 --> 02:18.800
And there came a voice from heaven, saying,

02:19.160 --> 02:25.020
Thou art my beloved Son, in whom I am well pleased.

02:25.840 --> 02:30.660
And immediately the Spirit driveth him into the wilderness.

02:31.620 --> 02:33.900
And he was there in the wilderness,

02:34.120 --> 02:37.580
Forty days, tempted of Satan,

02:38.080 --> 02:40.520
And was with the wild beast,

02:41.040 --> 02:43.520
And the angels ministered unto him.

02:44.320 --> 02:48.240
Now, after that John was put in prison,

02:48.840 --> 02:51.540
Jesus came into Galilee,

02:51.820 --> 02:55.980
Preaching the gospel of the kingdom of God,

02:56.360 --> 02:57.160
And saying,

02:57.640 --> 02:59.640
The time is fulfilled,

03:00.080 --> 03:02.780
And the kingdom of God is at hand.

03:03.180 --> 03:06.120
Repent ye, and believe the gospel.

03:06.120 --> 03:10.100
Now, as he walked by the sea of Galilee,

03:10.640 --> 03:14.160
He saw Simon and Andrew, his brother,

03:14.640 --> 03:18.120
Casting a net into the sea, for they were fishers.

03:18.220 --> 03:20.420
And Jesus said unto them,

03:20.600 --> 03:22.460
Come ye after me,

03:22.660 --> 03:26.240
And I will make you to become fishers of men.

03:26.700 --> 03:30.000
And straightway they forsook their nets and followed him.

03:30.460 --> 03:33.580
And when he had gone a little farther,

03:33.580 --> 03:37.740
Thence he saw James, the son of Zebedee,

03:37.900 --> 03:41.840
And John, his brother, who also were in the ship,

03:42.100 --> 03:43.260
Mending their nets.

03:43.820 --> 03:45.540
And straightway he called them,

03:45.640 --> 03:48.720
And they left their father Zebedee in the ship

03:48.720 --> 03:52.440
With the hired servants and went after him.

03:52.700 --> 03:55.380
And they went into Capernaum.

03:55.620 --> 03:58.120
And straightway on the Sabbath day,

03:58.500 --> 04:01.540
He entered into the synagogue and taught.

04:01.910 --> 04:04.400
And they were astonished at his doctrine,

04:04.860 --> 04:08.600
For he taught them as one that had authority,

04:08.940 --> 04:11.760
And not as the scribes.

04:11.920 --> 04:14.800
And there was in their synagogue a man

04:14.800 --> 04:17.000
With an unclean spirit.

04:17.360 --> 04:19.040
And he cried out, saying,

04:19.340 --> 04:22.680
Let us alone, what if we to do with thee,

04:22.780 --> 04:27.040
Thou Jesus of Nazareth, art thou come to destroy us?

04:27.040 --> 04:31.520
I know thee, who thou art, the holy one of God.

04:32.200 --> 04:34.560
And Jesus rebuked him, saying,

04:34.960 --> 04:37.860
Hold thy peace, and come out of him.

04:38.300 --> 04:40.840
And they were all amazed,

04:41.480 --> 04:45.640
In so much that they questioned among themselves, saying,

04:46.120 --> 04:50.000
What thing is this, what new doctrine is this?

04:50.300 --> 04:52.840
For with authority commandeth he,

04:52.840 --> 04:57.460
Even the unclean spirits, and they do obey him.

04:58.060 --> 05:00.500
And immediately his fame spread abroad,

05:00.840 --> 05:04.340
Throughout all the region round about Galilee.

05:04.880 --> 05:09.160
And forthwith, when they were come out of the synagogue,

05:09.580 --> 05:13.220
They entered into the house of Simon and Andrew,

05:13.620 --> 05:15.600
With James and John.

05:16.080 --> 05:21.260
But Simon's wife's mother lay sick of a fever and anon.

05:21.260 --> 05:26.400
They tell him of her, and he came and took her by the hand,

05:26.840 --> 05:30.260
And lifted her up, and immediately the fever left her,

05:30.680 --> 05:32.960
And she ministered unto them.

05:33.220 --> 05:36.120
And even when the sun did set,

05:36.380 --> 05:39.640
They brought unto him all that were diseased,

05:39.860 --> 05:42.540
And them that were possessed with devils,

05:42.740 --> 05:46.760
And all the city was gathered together at the door.

05:47.380 --> 05:51.420
And he healed many that were sick of divers' diseases,

05:52.060 --> 05:54.720
And cast out many devils, and suffered,

05:55.360 --> 05:58.260
Not the devils to speak because they knew him.

05:58.820 --> 06:03.520
And in the morning, rising up a great while before day,

06:03.660 --> 06:08.140
He went out and departed into a solitary place,

06:08.760 --> 06:13.980
And there prayed, And Simon and they that were with him

06:14.720 --> 06:17.560
Followed, and when they had found him,

06:17.660 --> 06:21.680
They said unto him, All men seek for thee.

06:22.060 --> 06:26.140
And he said unto them, Let us go into the next towns

06:26.140 --> 06:31.120
That I may preach there also, for therefore came I forth.

06:31.940 --> 06:36.000
And he preached in their synagogues throughout all Galilee,

06:36.400 --> 06:41.200
And cast out devils, and there came a leper to him,

06:41.200 --> 06:43.940
Beseeching him, and kneeling down to him,

06:44.140 --> 06:46.940
And saying unto him, If thou wilt,

06:47.480 --> 06:50.140
Thou canst make me clean.

06:50.780 --> 06:55.640
And Jesus, moved with compassion, put forth his hand,

06:55.980 --> 06:58.880
And touched him, and sayeth unto him,

06:59.320 --> 07:02.240
I will be thou clean.

07:02.880 --> 07:05.180
And as soon as he had spoken,

07:05.580 --> 07:09.040
Immediately the leprosy departed from him,

07:09.560 --> 07:14.120
And he was cleansed, and he straightly charged him,

07:14.480 --> 07:18.560
And forthwith sent him away, and sayeth unto him,

07:18.960 --> 07:23.040
See thou say nothing to any man, but go thy way,

07:23.680 --> 07:27.460
Show thyself to the priest, and offer for thy cleansing

07:27.460 --> 07:30.420
Those things which Moses commanded

07:30.880 --> 07:33.480
For a testimony unto them.

07:34.320 --> 07:39.020
But he went out and began to publish it much,

07:39.400 --> 07:41.660
And to blaze abroad the matter,

07:42.020 --> 07:44.920
In so much that Jesus could no more

07:44.920 --> 07:47.520
Openly enter into the city,

07:47.740 --> 07:51.180
But was without in desert places,

07:51.660 --> 07:55.320
And they came to him from every quarter.

07:56.200 --> 07:57.880
Chapter two.

07:58.920 --> 08:01.700
And again he entered into Capernaum,

08:01.700 --> 08:04.920
After some days, and it was noised

08:04.920 --> 08:08.800
That he was in the house, and straightway

08:08.800 --> 08:11.640
Many were gathered together, in so much that

08:11.640 --> 08:14.940
There was no room to receive them, no,

08:15.360 --> 08:17.520
Not so much as about the door,

08:17.740 --> 08:20.480
And he preached the word unto them,

08:20.660 --> 08:25.900
And they come unto him, bringing one sick of the palsy,

08:26.080 --> 08:29.760
Which was born of four, and when they could not

08:29.760 --> 08:32.560
Come nigh unto him for the press,

08:33.000 --> 08:35.920
They uncovered the roof where he was,

08:36.120 --> 08:40.400
And when they had broken it up, they let down the bed

08:40.400 --> 08:43.520
Wherein the sick of palsy lay.

08:44.120 --> 08:49.360
When Jesus saw their faith, he said unto the sick

08:50.320 --> 08:55.960
Of the palsy, son, thy sins be forgiven thee.

08:56.720 --> 09:00.520
But there was certain of the scribes sitting there

09:00.520 --> 09:02.780
And reasoning in their hearts,

09:03.280 --> 09:06.560
Why doth this man speak blasphemies?

09:07.180 --> 09:10.780
Who can forgive sins but God only?

09:11.440 --> 09:15.380
And immediately when Jesus perceived in his spirit

09:15.380 --> 09:18.200
That they so reasoned within themselves,

09:18.260 --> 09:21.580
He said unto them, why reason ye these things

09:21.580 --> 09:22.560
In your hearts?

09:23.120 --> 09:27.220
Whether it is easier to say to the sick of palsy,

09:27.500 --> 09:31.560
Thy sins be forgiven thee, or to say, arise,

09:32.080 --> 09:36.880
Take up thy bed and walk, but that ye may know

09:36.880 --> 09:41.860
That the Son of Man hath power on earth to forgive sins,

09:42.420 --> 09:47.260
He sayeth to the sick of the palsy, I say unto thee arise,

09:47.260 --> 09:52.660
And take up thy bed, and go thy way into thine house.

09:53.080 --> 09:56.880
And immediately he arose, took up the bed,

09:57.280 --> 10:00.180
And went forth before them all,

10:00.600 --> 10:06.140
In so much that they were all amazed and glorified God,

10:06.520 --> 10:09.780
Saying, we never saw it on this fashion.

10:10.060 --> 10:13.900
And he went forth again by the seaside,

10:13.900 --> 10:17.620
And all the multitude resorted unto him,

10:17.780 --> 10:19.080
And he taught them.

10:19.600 --> 10:24.900
And as he passed by, he saw Levi, the son of Alphaeus,

10:25.220 --> 10:27.280
Sitting at the receipt of custom,

10:27.600 --> 10:29.800
And said unto him, follow me.

10:30.540 --> 10:33.160
And he arose and followed him.

10:33.780 --> 10:37.660
And it came to pass that as Jesus said at meet

10:37.660 --> 10:40.940
In his house with publicans and sinners,

10:40.940 --> 10:45.700
Set also together with Jesus and his disciples.

10:46.120 --> 10:49.260
For there were many, and they followed him.

10:49.840 --> 10:52.760
And when the scribes and Pharisees saw him eat

10:52.760 --> 10:57.120
with publicans and sinners, they said unto his disciples,

10:57.440 --> 11:00.600
How is it that he eateth and drinketh

11:00.600 --> 11:02.840
with publicans and sinners?

11:03.380 --> 11:06.720
When Jesus heard it, he sayeth unto them,

11:07.280 --> 11:11.360
They that are whole have no need of the physician,

11:12.020 --> 11:13.340
but they that are sick.

11:14.100 --> 11:16.700
I came not to call the righteous,

11:17.360 --> 11:19.160
but sinners to repentance.

11:20.180 --> 11:24.260
And the disciples of John and of the Pharisees

11:24.260 --> 11:29.220
used to fast, and they come and say unto him,

11:29.500 --> 11:33.440
Why do the disciples of John and of the Pharisees fast?

11:33.440 --> 11:36.420
But thy disciples fast not.

11:37.040 --> 11:38.700
And Jesus said unto them,

11:39.040 --> 11:41.800
Can the children of the bride chamber fast

11:41.800 --> 11:44.040
while the bridegroom is with them?

11:44.560 --> 11:47.660
As long as they have the bridegroom with them,

11:47.780 --> 11:49.200
they cannot fast.

11:49.780 --> 11:53.240
But the days will come when the bridegroom

11:53.240 --> 11:55.320
shall be taken away from them,

11:55.360 --> 11:59.160
and then shall they fast in those days.

11:59.580 --> 12:06.100
No man also seweth a piece of new cloth on an old garment,

12:06.680 --> 12:09.880
else the new piece that filled it up

12:09.880 --> 12:14.840
taketh away from the old, and the rent is made worse.

12:15.500 --> 12:19.620
And no man putteth new wine into old bottles,

12:20.200 --> 12:23.100
else the new wine doth burst the bottles,

12:23.440 --> 12:27.780
and the wine is spilled, and the bottles will be marred.

12:27.780 --> 12:32.600
But new wine must be put into new bottles.

12:33.660 --> 12:37.900
And it came to pass that he went through the cornfields

12:37.900 --> 12:39.500
on the Sabbath day.

12:39.900 --> 12:42.760
And his disciples began as they went

12:42.760 --> 12:45.760
to pluck the ears of corn.

12:46.480 --> 12:49.000
And the Pharisees said unto him,

12:49.160 --> 12:53.980
Behold, why do they on the Sabbath day

12:53.980 --> 12:56.300
that which is not lawful?

12:56.780 --> 12:58.580
And he said unto them,

12:59.040 --> 13:01.480
Have ye never read what David did

13:01.480 --> 13:05.440
when he had need and wasn't hungered?

13:05.540 --> 13:08.420
He and they that were with him,

13:08.740 --> 13:11.240
how he went into the house of God

13:11.240 --> 13:14.300
in the days of Abathar, the high priest,

13:14.760 --> 13:16.640
and did eat the shewbread,

13:17.020 --> 13:21.400
which is not lawful to eat, but for the priest,

13:21.800 --> 13:24.820
and gave also to them which were with him?

13:25.000 --> 13:27.180
And he said unto them,

13:27.480 --> 13:33.100
The Sabbath was made for man and not man for the Sabbath.

13:33.960 --> 13:41.300
Therefore, the Son of Man is Lord also of the Sabbath.

13:42.460 --> 13:48.460
End of chapters one and two of the Gospel of Mark.

13:48.840 --> 13:52.740
Reading by Simon Wainwright.

13:55.580 --> 13:56.080
Thank you.

